#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Sajjhāyasutta "
msgstr "10. Recitation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.436, sc1
msgctxt "sn9.10:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

# NOTE: See my note on SN 21.4
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.10:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu yaṃ sudaṃ pubbe ativelaṃ sajjhāyabahulo viharati so aparena samayena appossukko tuṇhībhūto saṅkasāyati. "
msgstr "Now at that time that mendicant had previously been spending too much time in recitation. But some time later they adhered to passivity and silence. "

msgctxt "sn9.10:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno dhammaṃ asuṇantī yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Not hearing the teaching, the deity haunting that forest approached that mendicant, and addressed them in verse: "

# NOTE: BB has “Dhamma-stanzas” for dhammapadani. However the word appears only rarely in this sense in the EBTs, and where it does—at AN 4.191—it is clearly said with reference to all nine angas, not just verses. There, BB has “passages of the Dhamma”, which I follow.
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn9.10:2.1"
msgid "“Kasmā tuvaṃ dhammapadāni bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“Mendicant, why don’t you recite passages of the teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:2.2"
msgid "Nādhīyasi bhikkhuhi saṃvasanto; "
msgstr "living together with other mendicants? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:2.3"
msgid "Sutvāna dhammaṃ labhatippasādaṃ, "
msgstr "When you hear the teaching confidence grows; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:2.4"
msgid "Diṭṭheva dhamme labhatippasaṃsan”ti. "
msgstr "and the reciter is praised in the present life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.203, sc3
msgctxt "sn9.10:3.1"
msgid "“Ahu pure dhammapadesu chando, "
msgstr "“I used to be enthusiastic about passages of the teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:3.2"
msgid "Yāva virāgena samāgamimha; "
msgstr "so long as I’d not realized dispassion. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:3.3"
msgid "Yato virāgena samāgamimha, "
msgstr "But then I realized dispassion, which the good call "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:3.4"
msgid "Yaṃ kiñci diṭṭhaṃva sutaṃ mutaṃ vā; "
msgstr "the laying to rest by completely understanding "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.10:3.5"
msgid "Aññāya nikkhepanamāhu santo”ti. "
msgstr "whatever is seen, heard, and thought.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
